Team 👋

Now we are setting up the **MAIZU backend (server)**.

Follow every step slowly and carefully.

---

STEP 1 — Go to the backend folder

Open terminal and type:

cd maizu
cd backend

Press Enter.

You should now see something like:

maizu/backend >

---

STEP 2 — Create the backend project

Type:

npm init -y

Press Enter.

This creates a file called:

package.json

This file manages our backend project.

---

STEP 3 — Install Express

Type:

npm install express

Press Enter.

This installs Express (the tool we use to build the server).

---

STEP 4 — Install nodemon (important)

Type:

npm install nodemon --save-dev

Press Enter.

This helps the server restart automatically when we make changes.

---

STEP 5 — Create the server file

Inside the backend folder, create a file called:

server.js

---

STEP 6 — Add this code inside server.js

Copy and paste this:

const express = require("express")

const app = express()

app.use(express.json())

app.get("/", (req, res) => {
res.send("MAIZU backend is running 🚀")
})

const PORT = 5000

app.listen(PORT, () => {
console.log("Server running on port 5000")
})

Save the file.

---

STEP 7 — Add start commands

Open package.json

Find "scripts" and change it to:

"scripts": {
"start": "node server.js",
"dev": "nodemon server.js"
}

Save the file.

---

STEP 8 — Run the backend

In the terminal type:

npm run dev

Press Enter.

You should see:

Server running on port 5000

---

STEP 9 — Test the backend

Open your browser and go to:

http://localhost:5000

You should see:

MAIZU backend is running 🚀

---

If you see that message, your backend is working correctly ✅
